# .ncp-consumer — declares how galadriel pins NCP, for NCP's consumer-agnostic pin
# tooling (check-consumer-pins.sh / repin-ncp.sh). NCP holds no knowledge of this
# repo; it discovers us by globbing for this file. Galadriel deliberately pins
# the immutable release commit rather than trusting a movable tag. Revision rows
# also record the consumer-declared release label used by the coordinated checker;
# NCP's repinner derives the commit from the canonical local tag.
# These revision row kinds require NCP consumer tooling at or after commit
# 205384508d619923e05aef192bedaeb57cf665fc. The pinned v0.8.0 runtime checker
# predates them and can skip both rows; Galadriel's feature-graph gate therefore
# rejects an empty, unknown, legacy, partial, or drifted local descriptor itself.
# The default CLI graph has no NCP dependency. ncp-core is a direct dependency of
# the galadriel-ncp workspace crate and therefore of galadriel-eval; the CLI's
# off-by-default `ncp` feature selects that adapter. `ncp-live` additionally
# enables ncp-zenoh, Zenoh, and Tokio for the operational subscriber.
cargo_rev       Cargo.toml v0.8.0 2f5bd586d4bb20c90362bb6f5698b7f64057ba4e
cargo_lock_rev  Cargo.lock v0.8.0 2f5bd586d4bb20c90362bb6f5698b7f64057ba4e
